## A huge step forward in the Fight for Flash
![Thanks to everyone who has campaigned on Flash](https://diabetes-resources-
From 1st April 2019, Flash Glucose Monitoring should be available on
prescription across the UK to everyone who meets the NHS criteria - no matter
where you live. This is a huge step forward for people with type 1 diabetes
and means thousands more people will soon have access to this life-changing
This wouldn’t have happened without thousands of people across the diabetes
community campaigning to end the Flash postcode lottery over the last 18
However, the campaign also revealed a much wider problem with equal access to
all diabetes technology. We’ve launched a survey asking people to tell us
We want to better understand people's attitudes and experiences surrounding
diabetes technology, whether they have type 1, type 2, are a parent or carer
of someone living with diabetes and whether they are interested in accessing
diabetes technology or not. The survey will help us to develop our work
We want to hear from as many people as possible. Fill in the survey and tell
## What’s the Flash criteria in the UK?
The criteria to qualify for Flash still differs across the UK. Northern
Ireland, England and Wales have national criteria which need to be met to
qualify for Flash. In Scotland, it will depend on the health board area you
We’ve created four documents which set out exactly what criteria you need to
We know that, unfortunately, this still won’t mean everyone who could benefit
from Flash will be able to access it.
We’ll continue to work with the NHS to broaden the criteria and fight for
everyone who can benefit from Flash to be able to access it on prescription.
We’ve also got more advice on how to challenge the decision if you don’t meet
the NHS criteria and have issues getting Flash.
> “I was really impressed that Diabetes UK helped me to get the Freestyle
> Libre on prescription for flash glucose monitoring – that’s made a big
> difference to my mental and physical wellbeing.”
If you live in an area which is prescribing Flash but you're still struggling
to access it, please get in touch and let us know why by emailing
We’re continuing to fight to make sure everyone with diabetes can access the
